bib_record.title: Neutron pickup from Pt-194,Pt-196 and Pt-198.

free_txt: AVF cyclotron was used.
Particle identification for the reaction
deuterons was performed by a plastic scintillation
counter behind the focal-plane detector for a
measurement of the total energy, and by the demand for
the proper relative time of flight of the deuterons
from the target to the scintillator with respect to the
ratio frequency of the cyclotron.
The uncertainty in the absolute cross
sections was determined largely by the sensitivity of
the spectrometer solid angle to the location of the
beam sport on the target
Relative uncertainty
Error from error bars. No information about
source of uncertainty (probably, total).
AVF cyclotron was used.
The targets were evaporated from the highly enriched
Pt metal onto 20 mu-g/cm2 carbon backing.
The Pt-194 target with the thickness of 79 mu-g/cm2
was used.
Figs 2,3,4,11 from Nucl.Phys.,A290(1977)72
The Pt-198 target with the thickness of 84 mu-g/cm2
was used.
Figs 4,9,10 from Nucl.Phys.,A290(1977)72
The Pt-196 target with the thickness of 38 mu-g/cm2
was used.
Figs 5,6,7 from Nucl.Phys.,A290(1977)72
